{
  "name": "ObjectNav HM3D (built-in navigator)",
  "description": "HM3D ObjectNav agent assembled entirely from built-in glue (llmCall, textParse, historyLog) + basic_agent encoding nodes (image_analyze, obs_to_text) + the env_objnav nodeset's gym verbs. Loop: observe -> caption -> format obs -> LLM picks one of the 6 discrete actions -> step. The parse choice order matches the ObjectNav action space exactly (0=STOP 1=FORWARD 2=TURN_LEFT 3=TURN_RIGHT 4=LOOK_UP 5=LOOK_DOWN), so textParse's index IS the env action. No method-specific code — this graph exists to exercise env_objnav end-to-end; SR is not competitive (the paper-standard reference is VLFM, SR 52.5 on val). Benchmark step budget is 500 (enforced env-side via max_steps and the env panel's step_budget); the graph's 50 is a canvas-Play ceiling.",
  "step_budget": 50,
  "nodes": [
    {
      "id": "env_reset",
      "type": "env_objnav__reset",
      "label": "ObjNav: Reset",
      "position": { "x": 0, "y": 0 },
      "config": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "seed_obs",
      "type": "env_objnav__observe_egocentric",
      "label": "ObjNav: Observe (seed)",
      "position": { "x": 0, "y": 200 },
      "config": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "iter_in",
      "type": "iterIn",
      "label": "Iteration Gate",
      "position": { "x": 280, "y": 200 },
      "config": {
        "version": 3,
        "pairedWith": "iter_out",
        "initPorts": [
          {
            "name": "object_category",
            "wire_type": "TEXT",
            "persist": true,
            "required": true
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "caption",
      "type": "basic_agent__image_analyze",
      "label": "Vision: Analyze",
      "position": { "x": 560, "y": 320 },
      "config": {
        "temperature": 1.0
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "obs_to_text",
      "type": "basic_agent__obs_to_text",
      "label": "Obs: To Text",
      "position": { "x": 840, "y": 320 },
      "config": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "planner_llm",
      "type": "llmCall",
      "label": "LLM: Decide Action",
      "position": { "x": 1120, "y": 200 },
      "config": {
        "ports": [
          {
            "name": "object_category",
            "wire_type": "TEXT",
            "required": true
          },
          {
            "name": "observation",
            "wire_type": "TEXT",
            "required": true
          },
          {
            "name": "history",
            "wire_type": "TEXT",
            "required": false
          }
        ],
        "template": "Goal object: {object_category}\n\nCurrent observation:\n{observation}\n\nAction history:\n{history}\n\nYou are searching an unseen house for a {object_category}. Rooms connect through doorways and hallways — if the current view is a dead end or an unlikely room for this object, turn to find a new direction rather than pushing forward into a wall.\n\nChoose exactly one action: FORWARD (move 0.25m ahead), LEFT (turn 30 degrees), RIGHT (turn 30 degrees), LOOK_UP, LOOK_DOWN, or STOP (only when a {object_category} is clearly visible and within about 1 metre). Give one short sentence of reasoning, then write the action keyword alone on the last line.",
        "system_prompt": "You are an object-goal navigation agent inside an indoor environment. You explore efficiently and stop only when the goal object is right in front of you.",
        "profile": "",
        "temperature": 1.0,
        "max_tokens": 2000,
        "mode": "single_turn"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "parse_action",
      "type": "textParse",
      "label": "Parse Action",
      "position": { "x": 1400, "y": 200 },
      "config": {
        "mode": "choice",
        "choices": "STOP,FORWARD,LEFT,RIGHT,LOOK_UP,LOOK_DOWN",
        "scan": "last_line_first",
        "default": "FORWARD"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "history_log",
      "type": "historyLog",
      "label": "History Log",
      "position": { "x": 1680, "y": 380 },
      "config": {
        "max_entries": 20,
        "template": "Step {step}: {entry}"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "env_step",
      "type": "env_objnav__step_discrete",
      "label": "ObjNav: Step",
      "position": { "x": 1680, "y": 200 },
      "config": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "loop_obs",
      "type": "env_objnav__observe_egocentric",
      "label": "ObjNav: Observe (loop)",
      "position": { "x": 1960, "y": 320 },
      "config": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "iter_out",
      "type": "iterOut",
      "label": "Iteration End",
      "position": { "x": 2240, "y": 200 },
      "config": {
        "pairedWith": "iter_in",
        "ports": [
          {
            "name": "rgb",
            "wire_type": "IMAGE",
            "persist": true,
            "required": true
          },
          {
            "name": "pose",
            "wire_type": "POSE",
            "persist": true,
            "required": true
          },
          {
            "name": "history",
            "wire_type": "TEXT",
            "persist": true,
            "required": true
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "evaluate",
      "type": "env_objnav__evaluate",
      "label": "ObjNav: Evaluate",
      "position": { "x": 1960, "y": 500 },
      "config": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "obs_viewer",
      "type": "imageViewer",
      "label": "Observation",
      "position": { "x": 2240, "y": 560 },
      "config": {
        "rows": 1,
        "cols": 1,
        "ports": [
          {
            "name": "rgb",
            "wire_type": "IMAGE"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "reasoning_scroll",
      "type": "textScroll",
      "label": "LLM Reasoning",
      "position": { "x": 1120, "y": 560 },
      "config": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "action_log_viewer",
      "type": "actionLog",
      "label": "Action Log",
      "position": { "x": 1400, "y": 560 },
      "config": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "metrics_viewer",
      "type": "metrics",
      "label": "Metrics",
      "position": { "x": 1960, "y": 660 },
      "config": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "output_port__metrics",
      "type": "graphOut",
      "label": "metrics",
      "position": { "x": 2240, "y": 700 },
      "config": {
        "portName": "metrics",
        "wireType": "METRICS"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "note_probe",
      "type": "note",
      "label": "env_objnav probe graph",
      "position": { "x": 560, "y": -300 },
      "config": {
        "markdown": "**HM3D ObjectNav from built-in parts only**\n\nEvery reasoning node here ships with the platform (`llmCall`, `textParse`, `historyLog`) plus the standard `basic_agent` encoders. The env side is `env_objnav`'s four gym verbs: reset / observe_egocentric / step_discrete / evaluate.\n\n**Action mapping** — `textParse` choice order is the ObjectNav discrete action space, so `index` wires straight into `step_discrete.action`:\n\n| idx | action |\n|---|---|\n| 0 | STOP |\n| 1 | MOVE_FORWARD (0.25 m) |\n| 2 | TURN_LEFT (30°) |\n| 3 | TURN_RIGHT (30°) |\n| 4 | LOOK_UP |\n| 5 | LOOK_DOWN |\n\n**Scope**: this graph verifies the nodeset wiring end-to-end. It is *not* a competitive method — the paper-standard reference on this benchmark is VLFM (SR 52.5 / SPL 30.4 on val, habitat 0.2.4 + objectnav_hm3d_v1).\n\n**Episode selection** is env-panel-owned (dataset hm3d_v1/hm3d_v2/mp3d_v1 → split val/val_mini → episode)."
      }
    }
  ],
